---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { COMPLIANCE, CONTACT } from '../site.config';

const jsonLd = [
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'WebPage',
    name: 'Privacy Policy',
    url: 'https://prosperityservicesgroup.com/privacy',
  },
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    itemListElement: [
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://prosperityservicesgroup.com/' },
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Privacy Policy', item: 'https://prosperityservicesgroup.com/privacy' },
    ],
  },
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Prosperity Services Group"
  description="How Prosperity Services Group collects, uses, and protects the information you share with us."
  path="/privacy"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-gold">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="subhead">Effective Date: July 14, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container legal">
      <p>
        Prosperity Services Group is a fixed indexed annuity and retirement income planning
        resource operated by Price Services Group LLC ("Price Services Group," "Prosperity
        Services Group," "we," "us," or "our"), in connection with a licensed independent
        insurance agent, Kayla Price (NPN 18530055). This Privacy Policy explains what
        information we collect through prosperityservicesgroup.com (the "Site"), how we use it,
        and the choices available to you. By using the Site, you agree to the practices
        described in this Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Information you provide directly.</strong> When you fill out a form on the
          Site — such as requesting the free PSG Annuity Guide, scheduling a consultation, or
          contacting us — we collect information such as your name, email address, phone
          number, ZIP code, and any other details you choose to provide.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Automatically collected information.</strong> We automatically collect
          technical information when you visit, including your IP address, browser type, device
          type, referring URL, pages viewed, and time spent on the Site, through cookies and
          similar technologies described in Section 5.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Communications.</strong> If you contact us by phone, email, or chat, we retain
          a record of that communication, including any information you voluntarily provide.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Create and maintain a contact record for you in our customer relationship
          management system (GoHighLevel, "GHL"), so we can respond to your requests and follow
          up appropriately;</li>
        <li>Deliver the "PSG Annuity Guide" PDF and any other requested materials to the email
          address you provide;</li>
        <li>Contact you by phone, text, or email to schedule or discuss a complimentary,
          no-pressure consultation with a licensed agent;</li>
        <li>Improve the Site's content, usability, and performance; and</li>
        <li>Comply with legal, regulatory, and recordkeeping obligations applicable to licensed
          insurance agents.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Consent to Contact (TCPA Disclosure)</h2>
      <p>
        By submitting a form on this Site and providing your telephone number and/or email
        address, you expressly consent to be contacted by Kayla Price and/or Prosperity
        Services Group LLC by telephone (including by automatic telephone dialing systems and
        prerecorded or artificial voice messages), text message (SMS), and email regarding
        annuities, safe money strategies, retirement income planning, and related insurance
        products and services, even if your number is listed on a Do Not Call registry. Message
        and data rates may apply. Consent to be contacted is not a condition of purchasing any
        product or service. You may revoke your consent at any time by replying "STOP" to any
        text message, clicking "unsubscribe" in any email, or contacting us using the
        information in Section 8.
      </p>

      <h2>4. PSG Annuity Guide Delivery</h2>
      <p>
        If you request the free "PSG Annuity Guide," we will use the email address you provide
        to deliver the guide and may follow up with related educational content and an
        invitation to schedule a consultation. You may unsubscribe from follow-up emails at any
        time using the link provided in each email.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
      <p>
        We use cookies, pixels, and similar technologies to operate the Site, remember your
        preferences, measure traffic and engagement, and support analytics and advertising
        tools. You can control cookies through your browser settings; disabling cookies may
        affect certain Site functionality. We do not knowingly sell personal information, as
        that term is defined under applicable state privacy laws.
      </p>

      <h2>6. How We Share Information</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share information with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Service providers who help us operate the Site and manage contacts, including our
          CRM provider (GoHighLevel) and email/SMS delivery platforms, under confidentiality
          obligations;</li>
        <li>Insurance carriers or business partners only where necessary to service a request
          you have affirmatively made; and</li>
        <li>Government authorities or regulators, where required by law.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Data Retention and Security</h2>
      <p>
        We retain contact and form information for as long as reasonably necessary to fulfill
        the purposes described in this Policy and to comply with applicable insurance
        recordkeeping requirements. We use commercially reasonable administrative and technical
        safeguards to protect your information, but no method of transmission or storage is
        completely secure.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your Choices and Rights</h2>
      <p>
        You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of the personal information we
        hold about you, or ask us to stop contacting you, by emailing {CONTACT.email} or calling
        {CONTACT.phone}. Depending on your state of residence, you may have additional rights
        under applicable privacy law.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Educational Content Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        Information on this Site is educational in nature and does not constitute financial,
        legal, tax, or investment advice specific to your situation, and is not a recommendation
        to purchase any particular annuity or insurance product. {COMPLIANCE.annuityDisclaimer}
        Kayla Price is a licensed independent insurance agent (NPN 18530055).
      </p>

      <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        This Site is not directed to individuals under the age of 18, and we do not knowingly
        collect personal information from children.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Effective Date" above reflects
        the most recent revision. Continued use of the Site after changes are posted constitutes
        acceptance of the updated Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy is governed by the laws of the State of North Carolina, without
        regard to its conflict of law principles.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this Privacy Policy may be directed to Kayla Price, licensed independent
        insurance agent (NPN 18530055), Prosperity Services Group LLC, at {CONTACT.email} or
        {CONTACT.phone}.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-dark) 0%, #2b1147 100%);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }
  .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .subhead { color: #e2d4f0; }
  .legal { max-width: 800px; }
  .legal h2 { margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 1.3rem; }
  .legal p, .legal li { color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; }
  .legal ul { padding-left: 1.4rem; }
</style>
